  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this paper we study kinetics of the first-order phase transitions in gauge theories with spontaneous symmetry breaking. A general theory of the decay of the metastable phase (false vacuum) at a finite temperature is developed. A number of concrete examples are considered, which will make it possible to study kinetics of phase transitions in a wide class of theories without complicated computer calculations.</subfield>
